description: Exploit and remediate a XXE exposure. XML documents, among other features, allow the definition of XML entities by providing a substitution string in the form of a URI. The XML parser can access the contents of this URI and embed these contents back into the XML document for further processing. This could be exploited by an attacker to read arbitrary files on the server.
topics: Improper Restriction of XML External Entity Reference
title: XML Entity Expansion (XXE)
trophyDescription: The candidate can remediate simple XXE exposures in Java.

infoList.title: Starting the exercise
infoList.description: When starting the exercise you will be presented with an Ubuntu desktop. Wait for Eclipse IDE and Firefox to launch.

infoList.title: Eclipse
infoList.description: Switch to Eclipse, click on the "Servers" tab, then click on "Start the Server" to launch the application server.

infoList.title: Firefox
infoList.description: Switch to Firefox, browse to: http://www.vulnerableapp.com:8050 . Login to the Vulnerable Application using the following credentials: user / password

infoList.title: Finishing the exercise
infoList.description: When you have completed the exercise, browse to Running Exercises" and click on "Mark Completed". Provisional results will be available in the "History" tab.

infoList.title: Troubleshooting
infoList.description: Restore source code: if you accidentally break the app's functionality, you can reset the app to the original source code using the shell script at: /home/rtf/Desktop/RTF/restoreSource.sh

flagList.instructions: Remediate the XXE exposure by editing the class actions.StorePostAction

hint.text: Disable DTD resolution when creating the DocumentBuilderFactory object in actions.StorePostAction class

flagList.instructions: When storing a new post, an XML file is created client-side and sent to the server for storage. Manipulate the request to send a malicious XML file to retrieve the contents of the /etc/password file. Read the Exercise's Reference file for further instructions.

hint.text: Reference the Exercise's Reference document for instructions on how to exploit this issue.
